## Implementation Steps

### Step 1 — Scaffold the monorepo

Set up a monorepo workspace (e.g., using `pnpm workspaces` or `turborepo`) at the root of `patchhive-sites/`. Create the `apps/` and `packages/` directories. Choose a static site framework (e.g., Next.js with static export, Astro, or similar) and initialize it consistently across all apps so they share the same build pipeline.

### Step 2 — Build the shared `packages/ui` design system

Create the following shared components in `packages/ui/`:

- `Nav` — logo, product badge, all-products dropdown, CTA button
- `Hero` — headline, subhead, CTA button, secondary link, optional mockup slot
- `ProblemSection` — title + bullet list
- `HowItWorksSection` — numbered steps with icon + title + description
- `WhoItsForSection` — target user description + optional persona card
- `WhyDifferentSection` — differentiator bullets
- `CTABanner` — repeated CTA + trust line
- `Footer` — umbrella link, product grid, HiveCore badge, external links
- `ProductCard` — used on the umbrella site's product grid

Establish a shared color token system where each product has one accent color while the base palette (background, text, border) is shared.

### Step 3 — Build the PatchHive umbrella site (`apps/patchhive/`)

Compose the umbrella homepage using shared components:
- Hero with Option 2 headline and subhead from the doc
- Three-principles section (visibility, constrained automation, earned trust)
- Product grid using `ProductCard` for all 10 products in recommended launch order
- HiveCore feature section
- CTA banner: "Connect a repo" / "Start with maintenance visibility"
- Footer

### Step 4 — Build the HiveCore site (`apps/hivecore/`)

Compose using shared components with the unified workspace pitch. Feature list maps directly to the five bullet points in the doc's HiveCore section.

### Step 5 — Build each product site (Steps 5a–5j)

For each of the 10 product apps, compose the page using shared components and populate with the per-product content defined above. Work in recommended launch order:

- **5a** `apps/signalhive/` — highest priority, most complete content in doc
